CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 2, 1974, pg. 1, reads: "Will Continue to Fight - Pittsburgh Black Musicians say they will continue to fight against racial discrimination in union and music contractors. The group made their statement at a meeting last week at the Flamingo Hotel where they met with their lawyer, William B. Gould of California.  Pictured from left to right: Clyde Jackson, George Spaulding, Rubye Younge [Ruby Young], Charles Austin, Thomas 'Doc' Miller, 'Ducky' Kemp and Atty. William B. Gould, law professor at Stanford University.  Not pictured is Leroy Brown. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Musicians, from left: Clyde Jackson, George "Duke" Spaulding, Ruby Young Buchanan, Charles "Chuck" Austin, Thomas "Doc" Miller, "Ducky" Kemp, and Atty. William B. Gould, posed in Flamingo Club
